contributor: russia. armii︠a︡. glavnyĭ shtab. kartograficheskoe zavedenīe
description: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Common titles devised by cataloguer. Individual sheet titles in upper margin on some sheets. Sheets issued by the Imperial Russian government before the First World War (using old-orthography alphabet). Various editions of some sheets. Some sheets have been reissued and reprinted by German ("Auflagedruck 1917") and Polish mapping agencies. The sheets have row numbers (for example--Ri︠a︡d VII, Ri︠a︡d XXIII, Reihe XXXIII) and sheet numbers (for example--List 27, Blatt 12) in the upper margin. LC sheets imperfect: Holdings incomplete, variously torn, portions missing, fold-lined, annotated, mounted on cloth backing, encapsulated, any quadrangle sheets from the World-War-One period at scale 1:126,000 seem to have been included. LC has 25 map drawers for this set--approximately 1,800 sheets. Sheets variously include notes, diagrams, compilers' names, insets, and other data. Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image.
